A desktop AI/ML application built with [Tether](https://github.com/your-org/tether).

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- Node.js 18+
- Python 3.11+
- [uv](https://docs.astral.sh/uv/) (Python package manager)
- Rust (for Tauri)

### Development

1. Install dependencies:

```bash
pnpm install
cd src-python && uv sync
```

2. Run the development server:

```bash
# Terminal 1: Frontend
pnpm dev

# Terminal 2: Python backend
pnpm python:dev
```

Or run everything with Tauri:

```bash
pnpm tauri:dev
```

### Configuration

Copy `.env.example` to `.env` and configure:

```bash
cp .env.example .env
```

#### Local LLM Setup

1. Download a GGUF model (e.g., from [Hugging Face](https://huggingface.co/models?library=gguf))
2. Set `TETHER_MODEL_PATH` in `.env` to point to the model file

#### OpenAI API Setup

1. Get an API key from [OpenAI](https://platform.openai.com/)
2. Set `OPENAI_API_KEY` in `.env`
3. Set `TETHER_LLM_BACKEND=openai` in `.env`

## Building for Production

### Build the Python backend

```bash
pnpm python:build
```

### Build the complete app

```bash
pnpm tauri:build
```

The installer will be created in `src-tauri/target/release/bundle/`.

